            <div type="letter" xml:id="letter_1675_12_26_mm2lc_raw" n="117" facs="DSCF8717">
                <head type="raw" xml:lang="it" />
                <note resp="#smn" xml:id="archive-note">
                Collocazione II-C.P.1. lettera 117
                Lettere di Maria Mancini – 1676 [[actually 1675]]
                Numero d'ordine – 
                
                D. Maria Colonna-Mancini –
                
                =
                
                Lettera al Contestabile Colonna
                in data 26 Dicembre 1676 [[actually 1675]] da Madrid
                Sigillo mancante – tutta di pugno con biglietto per la Regina –
                
                oggetto:
                </note>
                <pb facs="DSCF8718"/>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[The image is a page of writing 15 cm wide; this first page of the letter and the second page are a single sheet, folded booklet-style in the middle.]]   
                </note>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName key="madrid">di madrid</placeName> 
                        <date when="1675-12-26">li 26 decem[[bre]] 1675</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>non si [[Marie first wrote "ci" and then changed the "c" to "s"]] sono ancora aute le letre benche il corriero sia arrivato questa matina percio non mi stendero molto solo vi diro che sono stata obligata per le ciarle continue [[Marie first started to write a word beginning with "p" and then changed the "p" to "c" and wrote "continue"]] che facevano antonia, &#233; naneta di apartarle da me, e se riconocero [[<hi rend="strike">del</hi>]] la misma falta en las otras lo mismo are, porque no <hi rend="sup">ai</hi> cosa peior que vivir con criadas habladoras spero che no lo trovarete male se [[<hi rend="strike">desda</hi>]] desiderate la mia quiete naneta con facilita potro inviarla in francia, &#233; antonia si potra metere in altro convento per</p>
                <pb facs="DSCF8719"/>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[The image is a partial page of writing 15 cm wide; the first page of the letter and this second page are a single sheet, folded booklet-style in the middle.]]    
                </note>
                <p>non imcomodare longamente questo, io stando in monastero due sole me bastano in tanto abraciando i figlioli &#233; agurandovi le sante feste resto per sempre vostra</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute></salute>
                    <signed><persName key="mancini-marie">M. M. C.</persName></signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="DSCF8720"/>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[The image is a page of writing, on a half-sheet of paper. It is written in landscape orientation (as opposed to portrait orientation), so the page is 21 cm wide and 15 cm high. The half-sheet is ripped along the top edge.]]
                </note>
                <note resp="#smn">
                [[This is a note addressed to the queen of Spain by Marie.]]
                </note>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Amiga y Señora mia esa carta me a de ha&#231;er V. M. el favor de embiar al nuntio para, que la remita en Roma en mano del condestable y en mismo tiempo le avisara V. M. de lo que pasa para <hi rend="sup">que</hi> escriva tambien [[<hi rend="strike">el</hi>]] y aprete al condestable [[something crossed out]] <hi rend="sup">que me dea</hi> licencia de ire en italia, a milano o en otro lugar del papa y <hi rend="sup">en</hi> todo esto le [[Marie first wrote "se" and then changed it to "le"]] encomiende V. M. el secreto porque no quiero llegui a saberlo don fernando ny otra persona; guarde dios a V. M. y perdone la llanesa</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
